maxAge is the number of seconds browsers should remember to prefer HTTPS. If passed a non-integer, the value is rounded down. It defaults to 365 days.includeSubDomains is a boolean which dictates whether to include the includeSubDomains directive, which makes this policy extend to subdomains. It defaults to true.preload is a boolean. If true, it adds the preload directive, expressing intent to add your HSTS policy to browsers. See the “Preloading Strict Transport Security” section on MDN for more. It defaults to false.// Sets "Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=123456; includeSubDomains"
